        <h1>Temporary changes to bus stopping arrangements at Waltham Cross bus station</h1>
        <div class="content-page-press-release">
        18 May 2011
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
<div class="main-and-aside r">
    <div class="main" role="main">

    <div class="article-teaser">
        From Monday 23 May several bus services will not be calling at Waltham Cross bus station while essential resurfacing and drainage works are undertaken.
        
    </div>



 <div class="on-this-page">
<p>Construction will take place Monday to Friday between 8:00 and 18:00 and will last for approximately four weeks. </p>
<p>Ongoing works mean&nbsp;the&nbsp;bus station will not be served by routes 217, 279, 317, 327, 491 and N279.</p>
<p>The next nearest bus stop is on the High Street.</p>
<p>Non-London buses routes 211, 212, 213, 240, 242, 250, 251, 255, 310, 310A, 311, C2, C3 and C4 will continue to serve the bus station using stop A and B only.</p>
<p>Details of stopping arrangements during the works will be available at local bus stops, around the bus station and on the Transport for London website at <a href="http://www.tfl.gov.uk">tfl.gov.uk</a>.&nbsp;</p>
<p>Bus station staff will also be available to advise passengers. <br></p>

     

        
        
        
